\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh I expect I did washing up and I did - I used to - 
bring in the coal for the fires and that sort of thing but - I didn't do any cooking. Only if it was - if I was going to cook something for myself. And the wife was out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you do any decorating, repairs or improvements in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Ye
s. Yes. That was all done in - by ourselves. My wife was quite good at painting and wallpaper hanging.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever dress, undress or bath the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
No. I used to some - when they were very - when Elsie was very little I don't think I ever d
id much with her - with my son but - didn't have to but - you see, I had to get - I had to catch a train at five minutes to seven which meant I had to be up pretty early and so while my wife got up and went downstairs to - cook the breakfast I used to - w
h
ile Elsie was very little you know, up 'til she was about two years old. I used to get her out of her cot and put her clothes on and - while she used to dance and la la la at the top of her voice, dance like anything, so I had to - holding the bedrail, it
 
was old fashioned bed you know with an iron rail, holding the bedrail and she used to - holding the bedrail and dancing and kicking and that kind of thing and I was trying to get her clothes on. Dragging this arm off while I stuck her thing on there and t
hen dragging the other arm off and get that arm into it. She was always full of beans. But that was all I used to do of course as soon as ever they got a bit - she got a bit older she could put her own things on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever read aloud to them or tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
I don't know - I think I used to read to them sometimes - out of a children's story books and show 'em the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Would you look after them if your wife was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your children have any regular household tasks to help you or your wife?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
I couldn't tell you, I don't - I couldn't tell you, they may have done when they got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Do you know what time they went to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh well, fairly early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Who put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well it's - their mother always used to see to that part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did they share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
They - they might have shared a bedroom when they were very little but - after that they had a room each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 You had three bedrooms there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you have a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When would the children have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When they got dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes. When they were little they did anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When did they have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well whenever it was necessary, you know
, the - children was - had plenty of time to play and had a garden to play in and - and I expect they got changed a few times frequently but you see I didn't see much of them in the day time because I didn't get - I was a long way away, I was in London al
l the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Where were the meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
In the - in the living room. There was a kitchen and there was a living room - between that was - a front room and behind that was the living room and at the side of the front room was the - was the - a lit
tle - the passage and the staircase going up to - out of which there was a staircase going up - to the upstairs and the end of the passageway was the kitchen. And the meals were prepared in the kitchen and eaten in the - living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No. No, we always used to that - room to eat in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Where did your wife do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did she cook on a range or did you have a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 First we cooked on an ordinary range
 - one of the old fashioned sort of ranges you know - black iron range with a - polished edges that was - you know, in the house, put in the house when we - took it over. Then eventually - we changed over to a gas cooker. See originally we had a copper in
 the kitchen. That was a gas copper to do the washing in you see. Then we changed over to a gas cooking - a gas cooker. That gave us more - room. And we had a - a whatsname - a geyser put in the bathroom to get hot water for both - for bath you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When was breakfast eaten - about what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well - of course I had my breakfast I should think about half past six so that I was in time to catch the five minutes to seven train. And as I told you see we used to - my wife used to nip downstairs and sta
rt cooking the breakfast and - while I used to put Elsie's clothes on when she was very little and so that she was ready to come downstairs and she used to go with me as - to a bend in the road when she - soon as ever she was losing sight of her mother sh
e'd ;- leave my - leave go of my hand and tear back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your children and your wife have their breakfast later then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh yes. Well the children did. You know, they - they - of course - the wife used to start her breakfast but she didn't - the ch
ildren didn't have their breakfast, not 'til later on. 'Cos she'd got to get the other one up and dressed and all the rest of it. So they used to - she might have had a - drop of cocoa or something like that. 'Cos I used to generally have cocoa with me br
eakfast. Not - not tea, cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 What did you generally have to eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I used to have a cup of cocoa, and some Quaker Oats or some such porridge material and slice of toast and then I used to catch the train and - five minutes to s
even - that was a threepenny train - that was threepence a day you see. Then I used to get up to Clerkenwell and go in and by the time we got there the - I used to - generally me father used to meet me up there and - at Bishopsgate or near Bishopsgate sta
t
ion - I used to get out at Bishopsgate station - walk straight down Great Eastern Street and Old Street to Goswell Road and along Goswell Road to the place where we worked. And - he used to meet on the part of the way down there. And - the - I'll tell you
 
in a minute - I'll tell you a story of providence saving my - saving our lives or saving my life rather. Going down Old Street like that. And - then we - by the time we got there the errand boy had got in, got the kettle boiling and made a big pot of tea.
 Then we used to - have our - a real breakfast then. We used to have a couple of slices of toast and - jam or marmalade you see and used to have a couple of mugs of tea and - and sort of another breakfast before we started work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you have an
ything different for breakfast on certain days such as Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh well - of course Sundays we used to generally have a cooked breakfast - perhaps we might have bacon and egg or something like that. Kipper or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How did you manage for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Miday? Well sometimes we used to take sandwiches with us. Because we always had a good meal when we got home at night, see, but - sometimes we used to take sandwiches with us. Other times we used to send the boy down to a li
ttle cook shop that was down the bottom of the road not very far away and he used to - we used to send him down there and he used to get us what we used to call a baby's head. And that - that was a steak and kidney pudding in a conical sort of dish, or it
 
was made in a conical sort of dish and the top came up round and white so that was how it got the idea of calling it baby's head. Used to send him down for a baby's head and - a couple - or we used to send him down with a mug and get half pint of soup or 
a
 pint of soup. 'Cos they used to make soup, we always used to reckon they made it out of the leavings that was on - left on the plates when the people had their meals in this cook shop, it was a sort of restaurant you see and people used to go in there an
d
 have their dinner and so we used to reckon they scraped off what was left on the plates into a pot and made this soup. But we didn't inquire too much as to what it was made of - it tasted all right so we used to - even if we had sandwiches we very often 
used to send him down there for some soup. So we very frequently had soup and that sort of thing, but they were - that's the kind of dinners we had. But we always had a real good dinner when we came home at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When you had your meal at night did the children have it with you as well?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh no, they had - of course when they were young they were gone to bed when we got home. Before I got home. You see they - the wife used to put them to bed at the proper house for children to go to bed. So we didn
't - they didn't have the same meals as we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 What sort of things did she cook for your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh they were - they were - the sort of thing you'd have for dinner in ordinary way - sometimes they were a slice or two of meat and some pota
toes and - cabbage or what not Peas - some vegetable according to what was in season. Sometimes it'd be some minced meat cooked up. Something pretty appetising and, you know, keep you going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How about meals on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well they were the usual m
eals you know, cooked dinner of some sort. Roasted meat and baked potatoes perhaps. Some vegetable - followed by a rice pudding and some fruit of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How about Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well they were about the same as what you'd have ordinarily - ther
e was nothing special about them. Just - tea and - a cake to follow the bread and butter and - whatever was going, lettuces or sales of some kind and, you know, just ordinary sort of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your wife make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well not - not to - not
 regularly to supply the home, she used to make bread sometimes as a special favour. We used to like a home made loaf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Didn't make any wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did she brew any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did she make any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well - no. We used to make a kind of a cough syrup. I don't quite remember all that was in it. We used to buy licorice and there was some kind of a seaweed I think there was - some stuff you put in made 
a kind of a jelly and used to boil them up together. It was very good - for easing a cough. That's the only sort of medicines we used to make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did she ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you grow your own vegetables or fruit or did you always buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well of course our garden was more or less limited, it was the usual suburban sort of garden. We had a plum tree in it and a pear tree. Used to get some fruit off those. And we had - sometimes used to grow cabbages and a few thing 
like that. Raspberry canes along the side of the garden. But of course they didn't - only supplied a very small portion of what we actually required.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh I couldn't tell you, we might have done but it'd be very occasionally.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you keep any livestock for the family - any hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
No. One time we had some rabbits. Kept some rabbits. Used to kill them and eat them but that was a very - small - effort. We didn't think 
much of it. We bought the rabbits actually for the children to have in a hut where they could go down and look at 'em and - feed 'em and all that. But they were never kind of pets. We never had 'em indoors or anything of that kind. We had a cat and a dog.
 A Collie dog and a cat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How many times a week would you say you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh I reckon I had meat of some sort or another every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Not that I know of. Might have bought a small tin of meat so as to
 make sandwiches with, something of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever have any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No. Didn't know any poachers. 'Course when we were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15740825 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392  there were plenty of estates close by where they could have done poaching and a few p
eople got a reputation for poaching but - didn't know any of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Did your wife ever have to go short so that you and the children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you have larger helpings of food than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 I
 don't think so, I couldn't tell, I had enough to eat and if I'd have wanted any more I could have had it but my wife was pretty - knowledgeable, she used to know about how much I wanted and so my dinner was just about the size I could eat and - she was p
retty good calculator in that way. Good cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were your children allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well only just to - join in a sort of conversation - they weren't bound over to silence or anything of that kind. And of course they weren't all
owed to leave - get away from the business of eating their meals, that was the main object, to get them to eat their meals and finish up what they'd - could eat and want and should - should eat by the time the meal was over - else we might have been eatin
g
 dinner at teatime if we left it to them to play in between. Have a mouthful and then start up something. They were kept reasonable limits you know that's - they could speak. They weren't made to keep quiet and they could ask - a question or anything of t
h
at kind in ordinary way - they were perfectly free to talk in that way but of course they were not allowed to - turn it into a - discussion group because it was necessary for them to eat their meals and get finished in a certain time. Well, a reasonable t
ime so that everybody could pack up and get about their business whatever they'd got to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well they were usually issued with a bit of e
verything but like all children some like some things and dislike others. As far as possible they were encouraged to eat every - something of everything. And of course their meals and what they were issued with for their meals was - chosen for being suita
ble for children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
What was you and your wife's attitude if they left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I don't know. If they were - if they left their food and weren't - had got no appetite for it we used to reckon there was something the matt
er with them and try and find out what was the matter, what was the reason for it but - mostly they ate all they were - as much as they ought to. They were both of them very healthy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 If there was something on the table that they wanted such as the sal
t, could they ask somebody to pass it to the - or did they have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes, they were all free to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did they have to hold their knife and fork in a cert
ain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well they were made to sit up near the table and - so they didn't spill things on the floor and - they - they were made to hold their knife in such a way that they couldn't cut - wasn't likely to cut themselves you k
now, to see - act in a kind of a civilized manner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were they allowed to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When could they leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well they had to wait 'til the family was ready to leave the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did all the family present for the meal sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh yes. We - it - when they were very tiny they sat in a special chair to keep - make them so that they were level with the table - take things - pick things up. Or for their mother to feed them as they - when
 they were quite little. But as soon as ever they could handle the knife and fork they were taught to use it and - they used - well I suppose both of them did actually, they were - when they were quite little I made Elsie a special knife. A small knife wi
t
h a - little horn handle so it was quite distinctive thing, I don't know what's happened to it now - she kept it for years. A little - a small knife about a three inch blade, something like that, so it was suitable for a very small child of course they ha
d it - of course Jack was the same. He had a special knife and a small spoon and so on so that they could handle them and used them. They could ask if they wanted any more to eat. They were free to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you all have regular places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes. We always sat in a regular order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
How was the meal served and by whom was it served and was there any special order in which you were served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well usually it was passed to the furtherest away from the - head of the table where fat
her and mother used to sit. And of course mother used to sit where - where it was nearest to the - fireplace where the - this kitcheners kind of thing where the - or when we - when they were big enough to - be - when we were sitting altogether we used to 
h
ave our meals in the sitting room - not in the kitchen because it was a very smallish kind of kitchen and there was the cooker one side of it and a big cupboard with glass doors where all the china and that sort of thing was kept. And - we used to - gener
a
lly eat in the other - room and it was - my wife used to generally fetch the meals in from the kitchen. The - meat and all stuff when it was taken out of the oven was kept on top the hot - hot stove keep it warm and it was fetched from there and placed on
 the table. Then she used to serve it out. She used to serving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
When the children were too young to feed themselves where did they sit and who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh well, they sat side of her - their mother. She fed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When did they join in the family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh soon as ever they could. They always sat at the table with us from a very - as soon as ever they were - old enough to sit up straight in a chair. That was from a very early age you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When your children were very young did you f
eel there was a right way and a wrong way to bring up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I don't know, we didn't trouble to ask any questions about it. Of course we'd boys been brought up in a family and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 It just came naturally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 That's right - and of course
 all our friends had got children. We - they just behaved naturally. No special - schemes - we didn't work to any special scheme. Of course they were all very happy together and they used to - like to be with us and of course they were always with their m
o
ther. Then I told you she used to take them to visit her sisters and to visit her mother and her mother's in law and they were always made a fuss of. And of course when they came home - when we were all together well then everybody was taking part in the 
conversations and all that went on. They were encouraged to look at picture books and read 'em and to paint - paint in the painting books that they'd got and - to do things like that, like things to interest 'em. Keep them occupied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your and your w
ife have the same ideas about bringing up children and did you talk about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh I don't know whether we talked about it - I expect we might have done. Certainly we both had the same ideas about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I don't know whether we - we was ever worried about them as far as ever I know. They were just - well, we didn't like it if they were ill and that sort of thing, they had the usual kind of things, meals and 
such things as that and Elsie had diphtheria once when she was - which was a much more dangerous kind of thing. Much more. She had to be taken away of course to an isolation hospital but - see, we were always in agreement, we never - never troubled to thi
nk about - who should do this or that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Your mother was alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well - I used to see her at least once a week because we used to go to the same meeting place - chapel as you call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
I couldn't tell you whether the wife did, I didn't have any occasion you see to discuss things with anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 And your mother-in-law was alive when the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you see anything of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 About how often would you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I should see - I expect I saw her the usual once a week I would have seen her more often if - you know, if I'd been home and about to do so. Oh yes, we were always very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Do you think your wife would have asked her advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh quite likely - yes. If there was any point that needed any explaining or that sort of thing but of course they was always talking about the children,
 you know, all the gang that you could call it. Well just what you right expect you see with all the much - we had things very much in common and the same ideas about things you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for you
r children in the way of affection, safety, food or discipline - anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well what - what did I - what did I ......?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 What did you feel you ought to do for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well we had - we had to keep them clothed and fed and encouraged t
o learn and to - behave themselves. It was a life work for a mother anyway. And kept them warm and such like and - take care that they behaved - cautiously, I mean to teach them to walk on the pavements and not run in the roads - rush out into the roads a
nd all that sort of thing and - we had that sort of interest in - at heart and of course that - that was part of the daily life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you think it was important to show them a lot of affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well I don't know we thought it was important, we did
 because of - you see it was quite a natural thing to do, see. We - we loved to get their attention and to encourage them and that sort of thing. And I expect - in a mild way boast about what they could do and things they said. Pleased to see they were ge
tting on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well they did but I don't know whether we - I suppose we should if the point - if anybody had asked us if we wanted to know we should have told 'em yes, I expect but it's a thing we did
n't think of. We expected them to. And they did - carried that on. And - as far as my daughter's concerned never wanted to do anything that we - that she felt she had to hide from us. My son, I'm afraid he did things that when he grew up a bit he was - in
c
lined to do things that he knew we wouldn't - be very pleased about. For instance he - they - when he - he used to go - when he was a schoolboy of course when he was growing up and getting to be a teenager he went to the grammar school at Colchester. And 
t
here was some excavations going on there some new road being made there or something and they discovered a lot of relics of ancient Britons and that and he - he played the top from school so he could go there and watch 'em digging and collect a bone or tw
o
 from the skeletons they dug up and - in the hope of getting a relic of two off 'em. But of course that was - that - noticed by the school authorities and they - they checked him at that. But that was - that'd be the only kind of thing which - they did wh
ich we didn't know about. As I say we were all together and behaved as reasonable kind of people would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh I don't know. Just - well they expect - we expected them to do what we wanted them to do, that
's say we expected to to act as though they were part of a family not be entirely selfish and to ignore - routine. They were expected to behave themselves and - act as they should in that respect. And to - if they were told to do things to do it. They nev
er refused to do it, if - they were never asked to do anything very extraordinary, if they had a task to do and they didn't do it well then they were called to account for it. But I don't know - I don't remember any outstanding examples of disobedience.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
When your children were young did you ever manage to leave them so you and your wife could go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 You wouldn't have anybody to sort of babysit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No. No I don't think we ever had anything of that at all. Cou
rse my sister-in-law was living nearby and - she would have given an eye to the children if we'd both been out but it was very, very seldom that that would happen - if ever. I don't remember outstanding - examples of that. She was always ready and if my w
ife wasn't up to the mark she would - readily do anything, fetch errands or - or anything of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I don't say - I shouldn't think we forbid them to do so but we - if they interfered they'd have been checked. But - they were always very welcome with all the grown ups that were ever in our place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well depends on what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Anything that you thought that was important for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well we expected them as - to behave reasonably and to - expect to have to stand on their own. And of course from a very early age they'd been - taken to Sunday school and given the facts of the matter, so to speak, they were tol
d - it was pointed out to them you see that they were responsible people and that what they did and said and even what they thought it had to be with regard to - God's laws which were meant for their benefit. And - any reasonable person checking things ov
e
r had to agree that that was right - that if everybody did exactly as they ought to there wouldn't be any trouble. No, it was pointed out to them you see that there were certain things which they absolutely mustn't do and - nor think of doing and that the
y
 were accountable for it and that of course it - it - the God who made the laws, he would help them to keep them and that although through human frailty everyone had broken those laws the judgement on them is - could be averted because Jesus, God's son ca
m
e into this world as a man, lived amongst men, knew exactly what was happening to them and it - was himself exposed to - and - bear the - and bore the same - and exposed himself to the same temptations and bore the same trials and as the record of his lif
e
 and character shows - he went down into the deepest trials and eventually was unjustly accused and cruelly put to death. How - such a thing can atone for our sins is beyond human comprehension but - as the old hymn put it - then in pity Jesus said, I'll 
b
ear the punishment instead. In some way his - what he did - what he had what he - how he behaved and what he did any how he suffered is placed to our account if we acknowledge how far we've gone astray and our unworthiness and seek forgiveness on account 
o
f the fact that he has taken that place and that was pointed out to the children and the responsibility of making a definite choice - and - which could be made and should be made at the earliest possible moment was pointed out to them and - that was the r
i
ght thing to do, the right way to act. Because obviously if we recognize the - that as the truth we - do - our best to follow his example and - acknowledge that we are and have done wrong and seek to do what is right and to serve him and to act in the sam
e
 way as he did in - to be unselfish and - kind and loving and - in every way follow his example. And be very thankful to think that we've escaped - the - what could mean eternal separation from every - everything that's good and - valuable. So we point th
a
t out that the choice must be there is - nobody else could it for them but it must be a definite choice, you know, it's not - a thing you could say, oh well, I'll do it tomorrow. Because you could do - keep on doing that all your life. But - it's like if 
-
 if they were in debt - owed a tremendous debt to somebody came along and said, well look, I'll pay it. The chance was there for 'em to accept the offer and hand over the account so that it could be settled for them. If they didn't do anything about it we
l
l it would remain unsettled. And the opportunity wasted. So we - and of course, nothing then - nothing but judgement was going to follow if they were actually in debt. So we sort of used that sort of illustration to point out the necessity to start right 
e
arly in life and - which they both did. I suppose that was the real chief object of all if we - if anybody asked us what our chief aim with regard to them, because of course we knew that whatever employment they followed that choice would always remain. O
f
 course we did help them to choose some kind of profession that - we sent them tom - to good schools and we sent them to college or - my daughter went to college and Jack did training in accountancy, he served a - not exactly - what they - they don't call
 
it apprenticeship he was articled to an accountant's to learn to be an accountant and of course he - when he came out of grammar school that's what he went into and became an accountant. But of course they both had to start with that object - with some ob
ject in view. Elsie was keen to be a teacher and so with that object in view she went to college when she left school and the same with Jack. He went into accountancy, he went - did the necessary training to become an accountant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you tell your chil
dren they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well in - I suppose yes in a limited sense - we - we encouraged them not to - stand up for themselves - not to be - subservient to everybody in that sense although - we certainly pointed ou
t to them that they were not to be average - be vengeful to - if someone - ever - have a grudge against anybody you see. Very much against that but - we - I don't know how whether I was right in actually doing so and how far you're justified in doing so t
o
 - if anybody hits you well - you're supposed to take your own part. That's a different thing from the - where - Jesus hit his - requirements of his followers he - told them - in a - in, see, that figurative language that if a man if someone struck you on
 
one cheek to turn the other so they could get a bugget for that but that of course was if they were - the idea - what he - the - the context of that was if they were - because they were Christians, if they were set upon for that reason they were not to fi
g
ht to defend their Christianity or their Christian walk in life but - if they - if some - if the laws for instance demanded that they should do this, that or the other they were to obey the laws but - even if they felt that they were being unjustly treate
d. Not to - seek revenge.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were there any children you discouraged your children from playing with?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well yes, we didn't like them playing with other children if the children were in the habit of swearing or doing things which we knew to be wrong.
 But - there was no great difficulty about this - that because of the children - the children that they played with were quite - ordinary sort of respectable children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well - if they did it deliberately they'd be punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How would you punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well - give 'em a strike with a cane mostly or, if it was necessary to punish them and they might have been sent to bed early or - denied something which they - valued, th
ey used to be given - they might be denied of some privilege or other but if it was very serious they were caned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Who would normally do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well I expect their mother. She had most to do with them but if - if it had been a serious matter as it
 - as did happen occasionally as I say with - with my son, then it was - it was - handed over to me and of course the threat was always held over them, well if you do that again I shall tell your father, see, and ask him to deal with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 About how often would you say you had to punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Do you remember any particular occasion when you punished them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
No, it - of course only once I can remember smacking Elsie myself and I think only about once I can remember caning the - my son deliberate - you know, on purpose because he had been very disobedient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both of you or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh no, both - both of us definitely and of course the very fact that from their earliest infancy they were compelled to - do what was right and behave properly I think that's why they didn't require much punishment later on because it - it was - obedience
 was sort of instilled in them when they were little and took notice of what you said. As well as the minor punishments like this - being found - felt - they felt they were in the bad and didn't like it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 When the children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Oh there was a fuss made of them. Of course they had presents on their birthday and they'd have a cake made for their tea and that sort of thing and they could invite a friend or so with - to come in and have tea with 'em because it was their birthday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Can you remember anything you did with your wife and children on Christmas Day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well of course we always had the special occasion - made a Christmas tree always and - some sort of jollifications.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you entertain any friends, neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well we used to usually got to our parents places on Christmas Day. And Boxing Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well - yes, I had a violin and Elsie learnt to play t
he piano. But - when the - when they were little we didn't have a piano. It was not regarded as being of - an absolute necessity - we aimed at getting one when - as soon as we could we did but you see the most of our weekends or the - the Sunday weekend -
 on the Sunday was spent at our relatives - our mother's place see where they'd got a piano and - people of our own age and that gathered round and as I said, used to sing and - make - enjoy ourselves in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did any of your family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No.
 My brother used to sing but he - he - not at home much because he - before he developed up that - talent for singing he'd gone out to Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your wife or your children sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No, none - none of us could sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Not on our own - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you play any games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your wife join in the games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes. We all did things together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you have books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes. Always plenty of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
We used to take a daily paper. Well I think at first the Daily Mirror and then later on when we got more - a bit more responsible the Daily Telegraph, we changed over to the Daily Telegraph.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
I think we used to have - I think the wife used to have a magazine. Of some sort. You know, where you get patterns out of - family magazine and we used to have what was called the Sunday School Chronicle, I don't know whether that's still p
ublished, it's a kind of a religious newspaper supposed - published once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
I did, yes. I don't think the wife did but I did. Belonged to the library in Clerkenwell because you see I was - that's where I had mor
e time to read in me dinner hour - than I had any other time in the day and I used to borrow books from the library at Clerkenwell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Where did you get books from - the ones you had in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh mostly they were given to us or we bought them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you and your wife read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Used to read to the children but not to each other. Well of course I did when the wife was ill but - course that was long before - that was long after 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Who would take them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well mostly the wife but if we went all out together then it was - at the weekend when I was available we used to go all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were they taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes, they were taken out on all occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever take the children out just on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you do anything on Bank Holidays with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 I expect so although mostly Bank Holidays was looked upon as 
a chance to work in the garden. Or do some decorating or something of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
No. No. No, I don't think we ever went away for a holiday. Not 'til very much later in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Could you tell me how you spent Sat
urdays in - those days - you were working up 'til about four o'clock weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Yes, well - worked - at first I had to work 'til four o'clock but eventually we went down to one o'clock - worked 'til one. I got home soon after two. Well of course so
metimes used to take the children out and - when Elsie grew up a little bit I - she used to come up to work - with me on the Saturday - hadn't got to go to school, she'd come up with me and - you know, had the ride in the train and walked with me to work 
and - played about there and thoroughly enjoyed herself. But you'll have to get her to tell you about that because I - she knows more about that than I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 How did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well, I told you we went to the chapel as you call it - the mee
ting place - we went in the morning and - in the afternoon and in the evening. With intervals for dinner and tea in between..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you and the children put on different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy your
self on Sunday or did you think it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well - I don't know as we thought it exactly wrong and I - we certainly didn't think it didn't matter. But our - elegance to not working and devoting our time to the meetings was to please our Saviour
 and God, to please them - not exactly to - because we thought it was wrong to - to disobey certain commandments we were glad of the opportunity to meet with others who thought the same as we did and show that we were thankful and appreciated it; apprecia
ted his love and kindness and - remember all the very - the good things that - the care taken of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you allow your children to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Well not exactly - not organised games certainly. We didn't allow them to - well didn't have to stop them - they didn't want to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 And you went to this meeting place three times a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Well it's what - called now Christian Brethren.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did your wife go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you belong to a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 They didn't have a choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did it have a temperance club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
No. There was I think somebody started up a - an idea but - of having a week night meeting with the temperance chiefly in mind but it wasn't very - enthusiastically rece
ived, it was just a couple of people that thought they ought to because of the evils of people - seeing the people getting drunk, we say this was a more or less common sight. Might see somebody laying in the gutter because they'd fallen down there or fell
 down in the middle of the road and people had rolled them into the gutter out of the way of the traffic but of course there's no motor cars - there's all horses. That sort of thing, galloping about. So that - there was never any organise temperance.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 You weren't a member of it anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you belong to any other clubs organised by this meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
No. No, there were no - were no clubs attached to it. The churches round about did have - football clubs and cricket clubs and all that sort
 of thing but there was never any organized thing of that kind at our Hall. Say, ladies - I think got up a sewing meeting at one time which they used to call a sewing meeting where they made - clothes and - patchwork blankets, patchwork quits and things w
hich they gave to missionary societies and that sort of thing. They used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 And your children went to Sunday school regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did they go to any adult or family services with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Oh yes, when they old enough, you know, 
when they were big enough to - be out late, as late in the evening as that, yes. Oh yes, they were taken with us. Well we wouldn't - when they were little we wouldn't like to have left 'em at home to do what they liked. See what I mean, you got to -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes, generally following the breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Was that on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 
Yes, that was every day really but of course the children weren't there when they were little because I didn't
 have breakfast with them. But I expect their mother might have read a chapter out of the Bible or a few verses out of the Bible and said a prayer with them. I couldn't say for sure - don't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Were your children taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Who taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3421161 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Their mother I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3417349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944392\charrsid14944392 Did you take an interest in politics?
